      <title>Important Conversations: The Spiritual and Ethical Dimensions of This Moment  at Cramton Auditorium</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/52452923720140/huge/d0e9831bdd6b9e1e5558b50875ed6bf94270ba9f.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Sun, 29 Mar 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>Join for "Important Conversations: The Spiritual and Ethical Dimensions of This Moment." Our featured dialogue guests will be Bishop William Barber II and Joy Reid. </p>

<p> </p>

<p>Bishop William J. Barber II, DMin, is a Professor in the Practice of Public Theology and Public Policy and Founding Director of the Center for Public Theology and Public Policy at Yale Divinity School. He serves as President and Senior Lecturer of Repairers of the Breach, Co-Chair of the Poor People’s Campaign: A National Call For Moral Revival, Bishop with The Fellowship of Affirming Ministries, and has been Pastor of Greenleaf Christian Church (Disciples of Christ), Goldsboro, NC, for the past 29 years.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Joy Reid is a New York Times bestselling author, a former Emmy nominated, two time NAACP Image Award winning primetime host at the artist formerly known as MSNBC and the current host of The Joy Reid Show streaming podcast.</p>

<p><a href="https://events.howard.edu/event/important-conversations-the-spiritual-and-ethical-dimensions-of-this-moment">View on site</a> | <a href="mailto:?subject=I found an interesting event%3A Important Conversations%3A The Spiritual and Ethical Dimensions of This Moment &amp;body=I found an interesting event you may like%3A%0A%0A%0ADate%3A Mar 29%2C 2026%0A%0ADescription%3A%0AJoin for %22Important Conversations%3A The Spiritual and Ethical Dimensions of This Moment.%22 Our featured dialogue guests will be Bishop William Barber II and Joy Reid. %0A%0A %0A%0ABishop William J. Barber II%2C DMin%2C is a Professor in the Practice of Public Theology and Public Policy and Founding Director of the Center for Public Theology and Public Policy at Yale Divinity School. He serves as President and Senior Lecturer of Repairers of the Breach%2C Co-Chair of the Poor People%E2%80%99s Campaign%3A A National Call For Moral Revival%2C Bishop with The Fellowship of Affirming Ministries%2C and has been Pastor of Greenleaf Christian Church %28Disciples of Christ%29%2C Goldsboro%2C NC%2C for the past 29 years.%0A%0A %0A%0AJoy Reid is a New York Times bestselling author%2C a former Emmy nominated%2C two time NAACP Image Award winning primetime host at the artist formerly known as MSNBC and the current host of The Joy Reid Show streaming podcast.%0A%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fevents.howard.edu%2Fevent%2Fimportant-conversations-the-spiritual-and-ethical-dimensions-of-this-moment%0A">Email this event</a></p></div></div>]]></description>
